Excellent. I added mozz cheese b/c the parm cheese we had was grated and I was concerned w/ it melting. I also added a dab of balsamic glaze I had on hand which added to flavor, but I think this recipe is great.

Rating: 4
Very tasty. I've also made this recipe using kale from my CSA box (stemmed, boiled in water for 5 minutes, cooled, squeezed dry, then chopped) and thought that it was equally good. I usually add a little more heavy cream, and prefer it with diced roasted red bell pepper instead of the sauteed bell pepper strips.

Rating: 4
Yum, yum, yum! The flavor was very nice and they're very pretty. My picky 10-year-old even liked them. I followed the suggestion of the Cook from Austin and used chopped frozen spinach, thawed and squeezed dry, instead of the fresh spinach. Other than that, made them exactly as the recipe states. Watch them carefully under the broiler, they don't take long.

Rating: 3
This was good, although I think one could cut out a few steps (spinach saute & chopping) by using frozen chopped spinach which has been thawed & squeezed dry...then do a quick saute w/ the prosciutto, garlic & cream to blend the flavors. The presentation is nice, however.

Rating: 2
Think there are better crostini's out there. I would add more whipping cream next time as I felt it to be a bit dry, especially after it sat out for awhile at cocktail party. Presentation is pretty and overall flavors are nice but not "saucy" enough.

Rating: 4
These were a big hit at my christmas party, even picky eaters ate them.

